          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>An <fr:em><fr:strong>inverse</fr:strong></fr:em> to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000X.xml" title="Quasi-inverse" addr="//erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-inverse</fr:link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi  \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ  \eta  \sim  \epsilon \circ  f]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\circ  g \circ  f \sim  f]]></fr:tex> relating the (<fr:em>a priori</fr:em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse. We will refer to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> equipped with an inverse as an <fr:em><fr:strong>invertible function</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
